                <h1 class="page-2-h1"> Learn about blood</h1>

                <h4>Blood is a vital fluid that courses through the human body, carrying out a myriad of essential
                    functions necessary for life.
                    Composed of various cells, proteins, and nutrients suspended in a liquid called plasma, blood plays
                    a critical role in maintaining
                    the body's equilibrium and ensuring its proper functioning. One of its primary functions is
                    transportation, as it delivers oxygen
                    from the lungs to every cell in the body and carries carbon dioxide back to the lungs for
                    exhalation. Additionally, blood transports
                    nutrients absorbed from the digestive system to tissues, organs, and cells, providing them with the
                    energy and building blocks
                    necessary for growth, repair, and maintenance.</h4>


