        <section id="three">

            <div class="page-3 ">
                <hr>
                <h3>Benefits of blood donation</h3>
                <li> Save lives: In India, millions require blood transfusions every year due to accidents, surgeries,
                    childbirth complications, blood disorders like thalassemia, and more. A single donation can help up
                    to three people, making a massive impact.</li>
                <li>Strengthens Your Community: Blood banks in India often face shortages. By donating, you directly
                    contribute to the local supply, ensuring life-saving blood is available for those in your community.
                </li>
                <li>Quick Health Check: Before each donation, you receive a mini-health screening that checks
                    temperature, blood pressure, pulse, and hemoglobin. This can potentially identify underlying health
                    issues early on.</li>
                <li>Boosts Your Health: Studies suggest regular blood donation, while maintaining iron levels, may
                    reduce the risk of heart disease and hemochromatosis (iron overload). </li>
                <li>Feel-Good Factor: Donating blood is a selfless act that brings a sense of satisfaction and
                    accomplishment. Knowing you've potentially saved lives can be incredibly rewarding.</li>
                <li>Builds New Blood Cells: Your body is a remarkable machine! After a donation, it ramps up production
                    of new red blood cells, keeping your circulatory system healthy.</li>
                <li>Rare Blood Type Advantage: If you have a rare blood type, your donation becomes even more critical
                    in India, where specific blood types are constantly in high demand.</li>
                <li>Manages Iron Levels: For people with conditions like hemochromatosis, regular blood donation can
                    help regulate iron levels in the body, preventing complications.</li>
                <li>Convenient and Time-Efficient: The donation process itself is relatively quick, taking about an
                    hour. Many blood donation camps are organized throughout India for added convenience.</li>
                <li>Contributes to Medical Advancement: Blood donation programs in India sometimes involve research
                    initiatives. Your contribution could potentially aid in developing new treatments or diagnostics.
                </li>
            </div>
